The paper discusses the challenges of communication over multiple parallel heterogeneous networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of forward error correction to reduce in-order delivery delay is a technique commonly used in multimedia systems (cs.MM) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the need to ensure delay constraints are met is a concern in systems and control (cs.SY).
